The paper deals with joint frame synchronization and channel estimation in communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), communication and networking (cs.COMM), signal processing (cs.SI), networked systems (cs.NI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of sparse channel estimation methods also suggests a potential connection to compressed sensing (cs.IT).
